<div id="c5">
<p>&#8220;Pointlessness, impracticality, waste&#8221;, those words are the opposite of MIT.  &#8220;Immaturity, innocence, naivety&#8221; perhaps describe those kids better.  About 20 years ago, Playboy named MIT one of the top 25 party schools in the nation.
In late July, you don&#8217;t see many parties and drunken MIT students.</p>

<p>In any case, the essence of an university is to foster the exchange of ideas, especially imaginative new ideas.  When you have a family to feed, you don&#8217;t have time to imagine.</p>

<p class="posted">posted by the MIT guy
